              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Data.Punk."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Federal Election Commission collects every campaign contribution over $200 — names, employers, occupations, dollar amounts. It's all public. Nobody made it visually navigable. Dark Money Map turns FEC data into a live force-directed network where political donations become glowing constellations you can fly through and interrogate with AI."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "FEC network builder"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — /api/fec chains three FEC API calls: candidate search → committee lookup → top-25 contributor pull. Returns a normalized graph of nodes (candidate, donors, PACs) and weighted edges (dollar amounts)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "The Oracle (Claude + tool use)"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — /api/chat gives Claude the full network JSON as context. When you ask a question, Claude calls the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "highlight_nodes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " tool with specific node IDs — the frontend listens for those SSE events and pulses the matching nodes gold in real time, before Claude's analysis even finishes streaming."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Streaming SSE"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — The Oracle's text and the graph highlight events share the same event stream. You see the network light up and the analysis appear simultaneously."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enter a politician name in Candidate mode (try: Biden, Trump, AOC, Pelosi) — or switch to Donor mode and enter a company or individual name"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch the force-directed graph animate: candidate node glows with party color, donor nodes fly in and settle into orbital clusters, gold particles stream along each edge proportional to donation size"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Hover any node to see the donor's name, amount, occupation, and employer. Click to isolate their connections."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ask "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "The Oracle"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " anything: \"Who gives to both parties?\" \"What's the largest single donation?\" \"Which industries dominate?\" — Claude highlights the relevant nodes as it answers."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
